Magnetic properties of materials The X-ray magnetic circular dichroism (XMCD) effect pro- vides a means of monitoring the magnitude and distribution of magnetic moments. Most typically, it is applied to the photo- ionisation of the p core electrons, as in the L(III) and L(II) edges. For the 3d transition elements these occur in a soft X-ray range (0.41 keV). The L(III) edge creates a 2p5 3/2 configuration in its excited state, whilst the higher energy L(II) edge is associated with the lower j value, viz. 2p51
